%F A005900 a(n) = 1^2 + 2^2 + ... + (n-1)^2 + n^2 + (n-1)^2 + ... + 2^2 + 1^2. - _Amarnath Murthy_, May 28 2001
%F A005900 G.f.: x * (1 + x)^2 / (1 - x)^4. a(n) = -a(-n) = (2*n^3 + n) / 3.
%F A005900 a(n) = ( ((n+1)^5-n^5) - (n^5-(n-1)^5) )/30. - Xavier Acloque, Oct 17 2003
%F A005900 a(n) is the sum of the products pq, where p and q are both positive and odd and p + q = 2n, e.g., a(4) = 7*1 + 5*3 + 3*5 + 1*7 = 44. - _Jon Perry_, May 17 2005
%F A005900 a(n) = 4*binomial(n,3) + 4*binomial(n,2) + binomial(n,1). - _Mitch Harris_, Jul 06 2006
%F A005900 a(n) = binomial(n+2,3) + 2*binomial(n+1,3) + binomial(n,3), (this pair generalizes; see A014820, the 4-cross polytope numbers).
%F A005900 Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n) = 3*gamma + 3*Psi((I*(1/2))*sqrt(2)) - (1/2)*(3*I)*Pi*coth((1/2)*Pi*sqrt(2)) - (1/2)*(3*I)*sqrt(2) = A175577, where I=sqrt(-1). - _Stephen Crowley_, Jul 14 2009
%F A005900 a(n) = A035597(n)/2. - _J. M. Bergot_, Jun 11 2012
%F A005900 a(n) = A000578(n) - 2*A000292(n-1) for n>0. - _J. M. Bergot_, Apr 05 2014
%F A005900 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4), n>3. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Sep 11 2015
%F A005900 E.g.f.: (1/3)*x*(3 + 6*x + 2*x^2)*exp(x). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Mar 16 2017
%F A005900 a(n) = (A002061(A002061(n+1)) - A002061(A002061(n)))/6. - _Daniel Poveda Parrilla_, Jun 10 2017
%F A005900 a(n) = 6*a(n-1)/(n-1) + a(n-2) for n > 1. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Jun 06 2018
%F A005900 Sum_{n >= 1} (-1)^(n+1)/(a(n)*a(n+1)) = 6*log(2) - 4 = 1/(6 + 2/(6 + 6/(6 + ... + n*(n-1)/(6 + ...)))). See A142983. - _Peter Bala_, Mar 06 2024
